==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hereticate
<hw>He*ret"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>haereticatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>haereticare</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
decide to be heresy or a heretic; to denounce as a heretic or
heretical.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And let no one be minded, on the score of my neoterism, to
<qex>hereticate</qex> me.</q> <rj><qau>Fitzed. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heretification</ent>⟦br⟧
